<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="306" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/816</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-15T17:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.35 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7980. I had an informal talk on December 4 with <persName corresp="#p_CRL1">Lord Robert Cecil</persName>, on the subject
                                treated in telegram 1653, December 1, 3 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d306fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_277">p.
                                    277</ref>.</note> from the Copenhagen Legation, which was
                                transmitted to the Department through me.</p>
                            <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> now informs me
                                that should you see fit to take any steps to prevent the recognition
                                of the Bolshevik government by neutral powers the British Government
                                is ready to lend its support.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>